<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/568905-in-the-beginning-of-the-book-i-think">In the beginning of the book I think Reynie has an internal conflict on determining whether he should trust Mr. Noland. He is many doubts about him but also likes him because he is smart. I think he chose to trust him because he is allowing him to help with the mission. What do you guys think?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_568905'><a id="like_count_community_question_568905" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/568905?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">1 like</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F2159225.The_Mysterious_Benedict_Society_and_the_Perilous_Journey">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/568905-in-the-beginning-of-the-book-i-think">6 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/568905-in-the-beginning-of-the-book-i-think">Add your answer</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

